Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_wire_variation_mode(25.10)                  set_wire_variation_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_wire_variation_mode - Defines wire variation analysis settings

Syntax
       set_wire_variation_mode

        [-help]

        [-reset]

        [-corner_sigma_multiplier <std::string>]

       [-correlation_type {statistical | correlated | binomial | corner}]

       [-disable_positive_slack_shift {true | false}]

        [-enable_seperate_wire_var_sigma_multiplier {true | false}]

       [-layer_avg_rpt {true | false}]

        [-rc_correlation_factor <<int>>]

        [-reset {true | false}]

       [-use_nsigma_coupling_capacitance {true | false}]

       [-use_nsigma_slew_for_timing_check {true | false}]

       [-wire_cell_variation_correlation {true | false}]

       [-wire_var_reporting_sigma_multiplier <<double>>]

       Defines wire variation analysis settings.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -reset Resets all or the specified options to their default value.

       -corner_sigma_multiplier <std::string>
              Provides scaling multiplier for corner scaling.

              Default: ""

       -correlation_type {statistical | correlated | binomial | corner}
              Provides control to handle inter-layer correlation. The accepted
              values are:

              * statistical:

              * binomial:

              * corner:

              * correlated:

              Default: statistical

       -disable_positive_slack_shift {true | false}
              Disables  positive slack shift caused by back end-of-line (BEOL)
              variation.

              Default: false

       -enable_seperate_wire_var_sigma_multiplier {true | false}
              Allows separate reporting sigma multiplier for wire variations.

              This parameter  should  be  used  along  with  -wire_var_report-
              ing_sigma_multiplier.

              Default: false

       -layer_avg_rpt {true | false}
              Enables layer averaging reporting.

              Default: false

       -rc_correlation_factor <<int>>
              Allows same layer R and C correlation. The accepted values are 1
              and -1.

              Default: 1

       -reset {true | false}
              Resets wire variation modes to the default value.

              Default: false

       -use_nsigma_coupling_capacitance {true | false}
              Allows to use mean and nSigma coupling capacitance.

              Default: false

       -use_nsigma_slew_for_timing_check {true | false}
              Enables  use  of  wire  variation-aware  slews  for timing check
              lookup.

              Default: false

       -wire_cell_variation_correlation {true | false}
              Controls whether to RSS or add  the  random-cell  variation  and
              wire variation for arrivals and slack.

              Default: false

       -wire_var_reporting_sigma_multiplier <<double>>
              Specifies  deterministic  sigma  multiplier  for  reporting BEOL
              variations.

              Default: 0

       Examples

              * The following command enables binomial mode:

                tempus> set_wire_variation_mode -correlation_type binomial

              * The following command can be used to consider the wire  varia-
                tion  and  random-cell  variation to be correlated, which will
                linearly add the wire and cell sigma instead of adding statis-
                tically:

                tempus> set_wire_variation_mode  -wire_cell_variation_correla-
                tion 1

              * The following command can be used to perform bounding analysis
                to  use  n*wireSigma  clock and data pins slews at endpoint to
                look-up the timing checks:

                tempus>   set_wire_variation_mode    -use_nsigma_slew_for_tim-
                ing_check true

              * The  follwoing  command configures wire variation analysis for
                statistical mode:

                tempus> set_wire_variation_mode -correlation_type  statistical
                -rc_correlation_factor -1

